## 1. Exposing the "Outdated List" Trap: The Pre-2021 vs. Post-2021 Reality

To understand why this scam is so prevalent, we must look at how the regulations evolved. 

Historically, under the old Medical Council of India (MCI) regime, the board did maintain an active list of recognized foreign institutions. However, on **November 18, 2021**, the NMC officially published the **Foreign Medical Graduate Licentiate (FMGL) Regulations**. This landmark gazette permanently dismantled the old "MCI list" system. 

Instead of maintaining a dynamic list of thousands of global colleges, the NMC shifted the legal burden entirely onto the student and parents. The NMC declared: *We will not give you a list. We will give you a strict, non-negotiable legal framework. Any foreign university that satisfies this framework is valid; any university that fails even one clause is invalid.*

### The Danger of Using the Agent’s "Approved PDF"

| What the Agent's Outdated PDF Shows | The Actual Post-2021 Legal Reality | The Career-Ending Trap |
| :--- | :--- | :--- |
| **B-Grade Russian / Kazakh Universities** | Teach clinical years in local languages (Bilingual Trap). | **Strictly Invalid.** NMC mandates 100% English medium for all 5.5 years. |
| **Philippines BS-MD Programs** | The BS degree is not counted in the 54-month core medical study. | **Strictly Invalid.** NMC requires 54 months of continuous core medical study. |
| **Cheap Central Asian Colleges** | Expect students to return to India for their clinical internship. | **Strictly Invalid.** NMC mandates a 12-month internship in the *same* foreign hospital. |
| **East European Sub-standard Seats** | Prevent international students from registering as local doctors. | **Strictly Invalid.** NMC requires full licensing rights on par with local citizens. |

By relying on an outdated "NMC List," you are looking at a system that was legally abolished five years ago. To protect your investment, you must evaluate the university against the active, post-2021 regulations yourself.

