## 3. Regulatory Freshness Update: Physical Verification & Onsite Mandates

To ensure maximum authority and compliance with Google's E-E-A-T guidelines, we must highlight the latest official directives issued in early 2026.

The NMC has issued a strict advisory regarding hands-on clinical exposure. In their latest public notice, the commission clarified that **online medical education is completely unrecognized in India**. 

Furthermore, for students who were forced to attend any classes online due to global disruptions, the NMC has mandated a compulsory physical, onsite **compensation clinical training** at their respective foreign universities. A verified physical certificate of this completed onsite training is now mandatory to register for the screening exam in India.

This underscores a critical truth: **NMC is prioritizing physical, hands-on, high-infrastructure medical training above all else.** 

